{{Infobox locomotive | name = Central Texas Gravel Locomotive #210 | powertype = Diesel electric | image = Central Texas Gravel Locomotive 210.jpg | caption = | builder = [[General Electric]] | builddate = 1953 | whytetype = | uicclass = | gauge = | leadingdiameter = | driverdiameter = | trailingdiameter = | length = | axleload = | weightondrivers = | locoweight = | tenderweight = | locotenderweight = | fueltype = Diesel | fuelcap = | watercap = | boilerpressure = | firearea = | fireboxarea = | superheaterarea = | cylindercount = | cylindersize = | valvegear = | valvetype = | tractiveeffort = | factorofadhesion = | operator = Central Texas Gravel, other industrial operators | operatorclass = | numinclass = | fleetnumbers = 210 | retiredate = 2005 | currentowner = The City of Pine Bluff, AR {{Infobox NRHP | name = Central Texas Gravel Locomotive #210 | embed = yes | nrhp_type = | image = | caption = | location = 1700 Port Rd., [[Pine Bluff, Arkansas]] | coordinates = {{coord|34|13|46|N|91|59|6|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Arkansas#USA | architect OR builder = General Electric | architecture = | added = May 24, 2007 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | refnum = 07000442<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} }} The '''Central Texas Gravel Locomotive No. 210''' is a historic diesel-electric switch locomotive at the [[Arkansas Railroad Museum]] in [[Pine Bluff, Arkansas]]. It was built by [[General Electric]] in 1956, and is a well-preserved example of the second generation of GE's 25-ton switching locomotives, a popular model used widely in freight yards throughout the nation and internationally. This model was first used by the Central Texas Gravel Company, and then by the Gifford-Hill Company, which operated it at yards in [[Shreveport, Louisiana]] and [[Eagle Hill, Arkansas]]. The locomotive was acquired by the museum in 2005, with plans to use it for moving rolling stock within its facilities.<ref name=NRHP>{{cite web|url=http://www.arkansaspreservation.com/National-Register-Listings/PDF/JE0688.nr.pdf|title=NRHP nomination for Central Texas Gravel Locomotive No. 210|publisher=Arkansas Preservation|accessdate=2015-11-10}}</ref>
The locomotive was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2007.<ref name="nris"/>
