{{unreferenced|date=October 2008}}
{{Infobox book | name = Corporal to Field Officer | title_orig = | translator = | image = | caption = | author = [[Captain (Canadian army and air force)|Captain]] H.P.E. Phillips, MC, and [[Lieutenant-Colonel (Canada)|Lieutenant-Colonel]] R. J. S. Langford | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Canada]] | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | genre = Military manual | publisher = Copp Clark | release_date = 1925, (4th edition, 1940) | english_release_date = | media_type = Print ([[softcover]], [[hardcover]]) | pages = Original 196, 4th edition 192 | isbn = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Corporal to Field Officer, 4th Edition Up To Date''''' was a [[reference work]] written by [[Captain (Canadian army and air force)|Captain]] H.P.E. Phillips, MC, and [[Lieutenant-Colonel (Canada)|Lieutenant-Colonel]] R. J. S. Langford, designed for use by [[Officer (armed forces)|officers]] and [[Non-commissioned officer|NCOs]] in the [[History of the Canadian Army|Canadian Army]] to contain the essentials of all the army's other military manuals. Originally published in 1925, the 4th edition was in use at the beginning of and during [[World War II]].
Both Captain Phillips and Lieutenant Colonel Langford were officers of [[The Royal Canadian Regiment]].
==Significance== This edition presents the pre-[[Blitzkrieg]] military thinking and [[order of battle]] for the Canadian army. Besides being a reference work on how the officers of the day would handle certain situations, it is also a historical look at an army just changing from horse cavalry and foot battalions to tanks and all-arms formations.
==References== {{Reflist}}
==External links== * [http://regimentalrogue.com/rcr_great_war_officers/rcr_offr_phillips_h.html Major Harold Preston Evans Phillips, M.C.]
{{DEFAULTSORT:Corporal To Field Officer}} [[Category:Military books]] [[Category:Handbooks and manuals]]
{{mil-book-stub}}

{{multiple issues| {{notability|date=November 2018}} {{unreferenced|date=November 2018}} }} {{Infobox book | name = Failed States: The Abuse of Power and the Assault on Democracy | image = Failed States.jpg | image_size = 200px | author = [[Noam Chomsky]] | publisher = [[Metropolitan Books]] | release_date = April 2006 | media_type = Print ([[Paperback]]) | pages = 320 | isbn = 0-8050-7912-2 | dewey= 327.73009/0511 22 | congress= E902 .C468 2006 | oclc= 63680087 }}
'''''Failed States: The Abuse of Power and the Assault on Democracy''''' is a book by [[Noam Chomsky]], first published in 2006, in which Chomsky argues that the United States is becoming a "[[failed state]]", and thus a danger to its own people and the world.
